# Environment Variables for Render

## Backend Environment Variables

Copy these to your Render backend service:

```
NODE_ENV=production
PORT=10000
MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://YOUR_USERNAME:YOUR_PASSWORD@YOUR_CLUSTER.mongodb.net/github-automation?retryWrites=true&w=majority
JWT_SECRET=your-minimum-32-character-super-secret-jwt-key-change-this
GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_your_github_personal_access_token_here
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here
FRONTEND_URL=https://your-frontend-name.onrender.com
```

## Frontend Environment Variables

Copy these to your Render frontend service:

```
NODE_ENV=production
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://your-backend-name.onrender.com
```

---

## How to Add in Render Dashboard

### For Backend Service:
1. Go to https://dashboard.render.com
2. Select your backend service
3. Click "Environment" in left sidebar
4. Click "Add Environment Variable"
5. Add each variable above (one at a time)
6. Click "Save Changes"

### For Frontend Service:
1. Select your frontend service
2. Click "Environment" in left sidebar
3. Add the frontend variables
4. Click "Save Changes"

