## Getting Your Values

### MONGODB_URI
1. Go to MongoDB Atlas: https://cloud.mongodb.com
2. Click "Connect" on your cluster
3. Choose "Connect your application"
4. Copy connection string
5. Replace `<password>` with your actual password
6. Replace `<username>` with your actual username

### JWT_SECRET
Generate a secure random string (at least 32 characters):
```bash
# PowerShell command to generate secure secret:
-join ((65..90) + (97..122) + (48..57) | Get-Random -Count 32 | % {[char]$_})
```

### GITHUB_TOKEN
1. GitHub ‚Üí Settings ‚Üí Developer Settings ‚Üí Personal Access Tokens
2. Generate new token (classic)
3. Select scopes: `repo`, `workflow`, `read:user`
4. Copy token (starts with `ghp_`)

### GEMINI_API_KEY
1. Visit: https://makersuite.google.com/app/apikey
2. Create API key
3. Copy key

### FRONTEND_URL and NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL
- After deploying each service, Render gives you a URL
- Format: `https://service-name.onrender.com`
- Use these for the respective variables

